claim.claim-text:
1. A method for slicing a shaped silicon ingot, the method comprising:
providing a single crystal silicon boule characterized by a cropped structure including a first end-face, a second end-face, and a length along an axis in an <100> crystallographic direction substantially vertically extending from the first end-face to the second end-face;
cutting the single crystal silicon boule substantially through a {110} crystallographic plane in parallel to the axis to separate the single crystal silicon boule into a first portion with a first surface and a second portion with a second surface, the first portion and the second portion being separated and not connected through any portion of the silicon boule, wherein the first surface of the first portion is a planar surface substantially along a {110} crystallographic plane, and the second surface of the second portion is a planar surface substantially along a {110} crystallographic plane;
exposing either the first surface of the first portion or the second surface of the second portion; and
performing a layer transfer process to form a single crystal silicon sheet from either the first surface of the first portion or from the second surface of the second portion.

2. A method for slicing a shaped silicon ingot, the method comprising:
providing a single crystal silicon boule characterized by a cropped structure including a first end-face, a second end-face, and a length along an axis in an <100> crystallographic direction substantially vertically extending from the first end-face to the second end-face;
cutting the single crystal silicon boule substantially through a {110} crystallographic plane in parallel to the axis to separate the single crystal silicon boule into a first portion with a first surface and a second portion with a second surface, the first portion and the second portion being separated and not connected through any portion of the silicon boule;
exposing either the first surface of the first portion or the second surface of the second portion; and
performing a layer transfer process to form a single crystal silicon sheet from either the first surface of the first portion or from the second surface of the second portion;
wherein the providing the single crystal silicon boule comprises:
growing a single crystal silicon ingot in the <100> crystallographic direction;
cutting the single crystal silicon ingot along a first cross section perpendicular to the <100> crystallographic direction to have the first end-face;
cropping partially side-sections of the single crystal silicon ingot to form a substantially squared cross section shape with at least one side face in one {110} crystallographic plane; and
cutting the single crystal silicon ingot along a second cross section perpendicular to the <100> crystallographic direction to have the second end-face, thereby obtaining the single crystal silicon boule.
